2135
01:16:42,810 --> 01:16:45,400
to find particles at different places.

2136
01:16:46,480 --> 01:16:49,980
You can Fourier transform the wave function,

2137
01:16:49,980 --> 01:16:53,400
and the Fourier transform is the wave function

2138
01:16:53,400 --> 01:16:54,660
in the momentum basis.

2139
01:16:55,420 --> 01:16:56,640
So while...

2140
01:16:56,640 --> 01:16:56,640
So I have a particle,

2141
01:16:56,640 --> 01:16:57,840
psi of x...

2142
01:17:09,580 --> 01:17:11,080
This is not the field operator,

2143
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:12,060
this is little psi.

2144
01:17:13,560 --> 01:17:16,320
Little psi is the wave function for a single particle.

2145
01:17:20,100 --> 01:17:21,680
Psi of x is the wave function,

2146
01:17:21,680 --> 01:17:23,840
and psi star of psi is the probability.

2147
01:17:26,640 --> 01:17:27,480
